  "body": "# ðŸž Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nHey guys, just stumbled upon this and wanted to make sure you are aware of it. \r\nPrism does not seem to enforce that the sequence_nr is strictly increasing when updating the metadata of a node.\r\n\r\n[Spec](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/master/specs/phase0/p2p-interface.md#metadata)\r\n> seq_number is a uint64 starting at 0 used to version the node's metadata. If any other field in the local MetaData changes, the node MUST increment seq_number by 1.\r\n\r\nThe spec states that nodes must increment the sequence nr. If for whatever reason a seq_nr is seen to decrement this should raise an alarm.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/c2615168d9af98c6c1a348b943b43dc158d57fbf/beacon-chain/sync/rpc_ping.go#L55-L72\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/c2615168d9af98c6c1a348b943b43dc158d57fbf/beacon-chain/sync/rpc_ping.go#L115-L123\r\n\r\nvalidation:\r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/c2615168d9af98c6c1a348b943b43dc158d57fbf/beacon-chain/sync/rpc_ping.go#L126-L139\r\n\r\n- ping response: check ping sequence nr > cached sequence nr\r\n- get metadata: check ping sequence nr > cached sequence nr \r\n- discuss whether this should be a reason to decrement the score of a node\r\n\r\n## ðŸ”¬ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n* hint a seq_nr that is lower than the one cached for the peer\r\n* code validates that `ping_sequence_nr != cached_sequence_nr` \r\n* metadata is updated w/o checking if seqnr is strictly increasing (or the one provided in the getMetadata call is actually > the one that is cached).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\ncheers,\r\n\r\ntin / consensys diligence\r\n",
